I r a n i a n r e c o r d s: An old record for 
<collectingCountry id="6E9EB5CBFF85122FFDFDFBDEC5CFF8D4" box="[636,698,1145,1167]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="467">Persia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="721888AAFF85122FFD4BFBDEC4FEF8D4" author="TRAUTMANN W" box="[714,907,1145,1167]" pageId="6" pageNumber="467" refId="ref8887" refString="TRAUTMANN W. (1927): Die Goldwespen Europas. G. Uschmann, Weimar, 194 pp." type="book" year="1927">TRAUTMANN 1927</bibRefCitation>
) was found in literature, without further information.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1636F55BFF85122FFF16FB1BC6ADF972" blockId="6.[151,1058,1210,1321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="467">
R e m a r k s 
<taxonomicName id="D1898ED8FF85122FFEB7FB1CC52BF88A" authority="(BRULLE)" baseAuthorityName="BRULLE" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[310,606,1210,1233]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignifrons">
<emphasis id="24FD2949FF85122FFEB7FB1CC680F88B" box="[310,501,1211,1232]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="467">Chrysura ignifrons</emphasis>
(BRULLÉ)
</taxonomicName>
was listed by 
<bibRefCitation id="721888AAFF85122FFD6BFB1BC4C3F88A" author="TRAUTMANN W" box="[746,950,1211,1233]" pageId="6" pageNumber="467" refId="ref8887" refString="TRAUTMANN W. (1927): Die Goldwespen Europas. G. Uschmann, Weimar, 194 pp." type="book" year="1927">TRAUTMANN (1927)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<collectingCountry id="6E9EB5CBFF85122FFC5FFB1CC36BF88A" box="[990,1054,1211,1233]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="467">Persia</collectingCountry>
, yet later considered as a doubtful identification by 
<bibRefCitation id="721888AAFF85122FFD17FB7EC424F8B4" author="ROSA P &amp; LOTFALIZADEH H" box="[662,849,1241,1263]" pageId="6" pageNumber="467" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref8286" refString="ROSA P., LOTFALIZADEH H. &amp; L. POURRAFEI (2013) First checklist of the chrysidid wasps (Hymenoptera: Chrysididae) of Iran. - Zootaxa 3700 (1): 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="2013">ROSA et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, because the citation could be also referable both to 
<emphasis id="24FD2949FF85122FFE5FFB51C5CAF950" box="[478,703,1270,1291]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="467">
<taxonomicName id="D1898ED8FF85122FFE5FFB51C54BF950" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" box="[478,574,1270,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysura</taxonomicName>
smaragdina
</emphasis>
(TRAUTMANN, 1926) or 
<emphasis id="24FD2949FF85122FFC43FB51C782F973" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="467">
<taxonomicName id="D1898ED8FF85122FFC43FB51C354F950" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" box="[962,1057,1270,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="468" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chrysura</taxonomicName>
anatolica
</emphasis>
(TRAUTMANN, 1926).
</paragraph>
